511
00:37:36,213 --> 00:37:38,010
Take drugs?
Deal drugs? Pimp?

512
00:37:38,253 --> 00:37:40,483
That kind of spin
can influence a grand jury.

513
00:37:40,733 --> 00:37:42,371
Get investigators to hit the streets.

514
00:37:42,613 --> 00:37:45,286
Every P.I. In town's an off-duty cop.

515
00:37:45,813 --> 00:37:48,452
Besides, why would we need a P. I...

516
00:37:48,693 --> 00:37:51,810
...when we got ourselves
a hotshot New York writer...

517
00:37:52,053 --> 00:37:53,805
...filling all the gaps?

518
00:37:56,173 --> 00:37:57,492
Take care, bubba.

519
00:38:17,453 --> 00:38:19,444
- Are you the flower man?
- No, I'm John Kelso.

520
00:38:19,693 --> 00:38:21,923
Good morning, I'm a writer
and wanted to ask you...

521
00:38:22,173 --> 00:38:24,562
If you're not the flower man,
leave me be.

522
00:38:24,813 --> 00:38:28,567
The Lady's in mourning, and
I haven't received a flower or a rose...

523
00:38:28,813 --> 00:38:31,725
...or anything to show for it.
Please leave me be.

524
00:38:35,213 --> 00:38:39,047
I know Billy Hanson used to live here.
I wanted to ask a few questions.

525
00:38:39,293 --> 00:38:41,966
And if it's an inappropriate time,
I'll come back later.

526
00:38:42,213 --> 00:38:46,889
I can't believe you're running around
ringing my doorbell. Where you from?

527
00:38:47,213 --> 00:38:48,885
Where are your manners?

528
00:38:49,133 --> 00:38:50,885
Just leave me be.

529
00:38:53,613 --> 00:38:55,729
My condolences.
I'll call...

530
00:38:56,493 --> 00:38:58,723
I'll come back another time, or...

531
00:40:22,573 --> 00:40:24,962
I apologize for the delay.

532
00:40:26,733 --> 00:40:31,443
Why, thank you. They're lovely.
They're absolutely lovely.

533
00:40:31,693 --> 00:40:34,412
I'd love to ask you a few questions,
if you have a minute.

534
00:40:34,893 --> 00:40:36,611
Is this your car?

535
00:40:38,573 --> 00:40:40,131
How about a ride home?

536
00:40:44,133 --> 00:40:45,248
Thank you.

537
00:40:53,893 --> 00:40:56,965
What I want to know is,
what is a white boy like you...

538
00:40:57,213 --> 00:41:01,525
...doing driving a big old brother's
jive-ass heap like this shit here?

539
00:41:01,773 --> 00:41:04,924
I just bought this.
I kind of like it. It's not a bad car.

540
00:41:05,173 --> 00:41:07,767
No, it's not bad.
Did I hurt your feelings?

541
00:41:08,013 --> 00:41:10,607
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to hurt your feelings.

542
00:41:10,853 --> 00:41:14,163
I can't help it.
I just call things out as I see it.

543
00:41:14,413 --> 00:41:16,290
I just can't help it.
I just do that.

544
00:41:16,773 --> 00:41:19,207
- One thing you needn't worry about.
- What's that?

545
00:41:19,453 --> 00:41:23,002
Ain't nobody going to try
to steal this piece of shit.

546
00:41:23,653 --> 00:41:26,963
I'm just practicing up till I can save
enough money to get my Rolls.

547
00:41:27,213 --> 00:41:30,011
Chablis is a pretty name.
It's unusual.

548
00:41:30,253 --> 00:41:34,326
Thank you. I got it off a wine bottle.
It's a show name.

549
00:41:34,573 --> 00:41:38,282
- You're an actress?
- I'm not an actress. I'm a showgirl.

550
00:41:38,533 --> 00:41:40,967
I work at the Pick-Up on Congress.

551
00:41:41,213 --> 00:41:44,888
I lip-synch, I emcee, I dance.
You know, shit like that.

552
00:41:45,133 --> 00:41:48,887
The person you see now
is just little old simple Chablis.

553
00:41:49,133 --> 00:41:50,452
But in the evenings...

554
00:41:50,693 --> 00:41:53,924
...when I put on my gowns
and my makeup...

555
00:41:54,173 --> 00:41:56,767
...and my jewelry and my perfume...

556
00:41:57,013 --> 00:41:59,163
...I become "The Lady Chablis."

557
00:42:01,573 --> 00:42:03,928
You are just so cute.

558
00:42:04,173 --> 00:42:06,448
A cool white wine for a cool black girl.

559
00:42:06,693 --> 00:42:09,730
And you're full of flattery too.

560
00:42:10,533 --> 00:42:14,890
It's getting hot up in here, honey.
My shots are kicking in.

561
00:42:16,413 --> 00:42:17,323
Excuse me?

562
00:42:17,573 --> 00:42:20,087
Yes, honey, my shots.
Never mind that.

563
00:42:20,333 --> 00:42:22,403
What'd you want to talk to me about?

564
00:42:23,933 --> 00:42:25,048
Billy Hanson.

565
00:42:26,973 --> 00:42:30,568
No. Billy's dead.
Case closed.

566
00:42:31,173 --> 00:42:32,572
Was he your boyfriend?

567
00:42:32,813 --> 00:42:34,326
Billy, my boyfriend?

568
00:42:34,573 --> 00:42:35,972
Were you two lovers?

569
00:42:36,773 --> 00:42:38,001
No. Hell, no.

570
00:42:38,253 --> 00:42:41,051
Billy was way too trashy for me, honey.
I'm a lady.

571
00:42:41,293 --> 00:42:43,932
However, he did date
my roommate Corinne for a while.

572
00:42:45,453 --> 00:42:49,082
The two of those
had some wild times together.

573
00:42:53,133 --> 00:42:56,443
- Those are beautiful.
- So, tell me more about Corinne.

574
00:42:57,173 --> 00:42:59,448
Corinne's like a lot of girls.

575
00:43:00,053 --> 00:43:03,284
She found herself attracted
to the wrong type of man.

576
00:43:04,093 --> 00:43:07,802
Billy was not the right type of man.
She thought she could change him.

577
00:43:08,053 --> 00:43:11,250
But there was no way of changing
that evil son of a bitch.

578
00:43:11,493 --> 00:43:13,961
- I'd love to speak to Corinne.
- I'd like to too.

579
00:43:14,213 --> 00:43:18,286
But she skipped town
owing me two months' rent.

580
00:43:18,533 --> 00:43:21,366
And Billy said he would pay for it,
but now he's...

581
00:43:23,893 --> 00:43:25,531
But you know...

582
00:43:25,773 --> 00:43:27,843
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

583
00:43:28,093 --> 00:43:30,812
But you know,
it's like my mama always said...

584
00:43:32,893 --> 00:43:34,849
..."Two tears in a bucket...

585
00:43:35,093 --> 00:43:37,209
...motherfuck it."

586
00:43:38,533 --> 00:43:39,886
I have to remember that one.

587
00:43:40,133 --> 00:43:42,408
Don't remember that one.
That's off-the-record.

588
00:43:50,053 --> 00:43:51,532
Let me get your door for you.

589
00:44:04,653 --> 00:44:06,086
Thank you, hon.

590
00:44:11,853 --> 00:44:15,641
In the phone book,
you were listed as F. De Veau.

591
00:44:17,573 --> 00:44:19,131
What's the "F" stand for?

592
00:44:20,973 --> 00:44:23,362
The "F" stands for Frank, hon.

593
00:44:23,613 --> 00:44:24,841
That's me.

594
00:44:38,853 --> 00:44:40,684
- She's a he.
- Correct.

595
00:44:40,853 --> 00:44:42,127
You're shitting me.

596
00:44:42,373 --> 00:44:45,092
If this thing heats up,
I think you'll want to talk to her.

597
00:44:45,333 --> 00:44:47,164
Proper folks don't discuss such things.

598
00:44:47,613 --> 00:44:49,444
She paints a rotten picture of Billy.

599
00:44:49,693 --> 00:44:52,844
Let me tell you a story.
There was a judge here years ago.

600
00:44:53,093 --> 00:44:56,563
His oldest boy was messing around
with a gangster's girlfriend.

601
00:44:57,533 --> 00:44:59,410
One morning they found him...

602
00:45:00,053 --> 00:45:03,443
...lying under the porch
with his privates tucked into his lapel.

603
00:45:05,813 --> 00:45:07,804
Dead men tell no tales.

604
00:45:08,693 --> 00:45:10,684
Next day, headline read...

605
00:45:10,933 --> 00:45:12,764
..."Fall From Porch Proves Fatal."

606
00:45:13,973 --> 00:45:15,804
Some fall.
What's your point?

607
00:45:16,413 --> 00:45:20,531
Saving face in the light of unpleasant
circumstances is the Savannah way.

608
00:45:21,973 --> 00:45:24,612
I'll try to track down that real girl.
Corinne, you said?

609
00:45:25,213 --> 00:45:26,931
Well, I got to skedaddle.

610
00:45:27,173 --> 00:45:30,131
Doing Christmas at Tybee Island.
We got all sorts of folks coming.

611
00:45:30,373 --> 00:45:31,692
Have a great Christmas.

612
00:45:31,933 --> 00:45:34,288
- You too, John.
- See you later, Uga.

613
00:45:43,133 --> 00:45:45,169
Merry Christmas!

614
00:46:27,373 --> 00:46:28,931
He's got it on a string!

615
00:46:50,853 --> 00:46:52,411
Luther's not eating!

616
00:47:00,493 --> 00:47:01,687
Check, please.

617
00:47:03,013 --> 00:47:04,332
You didn't like it?

618
00:47:04,773 --> 00:47:07,048
No, they were very good.
Excellent.

619
00:47:09,493 --> 00:47:10,892
What was in the vial?

620
00:47:12,493 --> 00:47:15,690
He says it's enough poison
to kill everybody in the county.

621
00:47:17,493 --> 00:47:19,449
If he eats and it's a good day...

622
00:47:19,693 --> 00:47:20,603
...fine.

623
00:47:21,293 --> 00:47:22,408
If he doesn't eat...

624
00:47:22,653 --> 00:47:26,931
...let's put it this way: If I were
you, I wouldn't drink the water today.

625
00:47:27,333 --> 00:47:28,846
Where does he put the poison?

626
00:47:29,093 --> 00:47:31,402
In the water supply system.

627
00:47:33,773 --> 00:47:35,206
Is that true?
Do you believe that?

628
00:47:37,253 --> 00:47:41,644
I've lived here a long time, honey.
I believe most anything about anybody.

629
00:47:45,133 --> 00:47:46,407
Where are we going?

630
00:47:46,653 --> 00:47:48,530
Patience, dear boy.

631
00:47:52,893 --> 00:47:56,772
It's time you meet the most important
member of my defense team.

632
00:47:57,253 --> 00:47:58,652
We're going to the cemetery?

633
00:47:58,893 --> 00:48:02,363
Not Bonaventure.
The colored cemetery's down the road.

634
00:49:03,253 --> 00:49:06,290
Looks like we got the garden
all to ourselves tonight.

635
00:49:08,933 --> 00:49:10,332
Meet Minerva.

636
00:49:13,333 --> 00:49:14,288
How do you do?

637
00:49:15,973 --> 00:49:17,691
You trying to work me, boy?

638
00:49:18,973 --> 00:49:21,043
Put that hand back in your pocket.

639
00:49:28,533 --> 00:49:30,489
I feel sorry for you.

640
00:49:31,293 --> 00:49:32,885
Do tell, Minerva.

641
00:49:33,373 --> 00:49:35,284
He think nobody love him.

642
00:49:38,813 --> 00:49:40,531
That's silly.
We've never met.

643
00:49:43,413 --> 00:49:44,812
You got a hole in you.

644
00:49:45,053 --> 00:49:46,611
Too many questions.

645
00:49:46,853 --> 00:49:50,971
Don't know whether to be this way
or that without the answers.

646
00:49:53,173 --> 00:49:55,733
There ain't no answers.

647
00:50:00,933 --> 00:50:04,209
You come a long way to find that out,
didn't you?

648
00:50:07,173 --> 00:50:09,971
Now we got to get to work.
You bring the money?

649
00:50:12,253 --> 00:50:13,322
Put it on the grave.

650
00:50:15,653 --> 00:50:18,167
Kiss it first,
so it come back to you.

651
00:50:20,533 --> 00:50:22,683
You bring the shiny dimes?

652
00:50:29,733 --> 00:50:30,848
Bury them.

653
00:50:31,973 --> 00:50:34,965
He's working hard against you, James.

654
00:50:35,253 --> 00:50:36,891
Who? Dr. Buzzard?

655
00:50:39,133 --> 00:50:41,169
The boy. The dead boy.

656
00:50:41,693 --> 00:50:43,684
Oh, Billy.
That doesn't surprise us.

657
00:50:43,933 --> 00:50:45,332
Dr. Buzzard?

658
00:50:47,413 --> 00:50:48,846
Ain't got much dead time left.

659
00:50:49,893 --> 00:50:51,087
Dead time?

660
00:50:51,973 --> 00:50:53,531
Lasts an hour.

661
00:50:53,853 --> 00:50:57,084
Half-hour before midnight
till half past.

662
00:50:57,533 --> 00:51:00,411
Half-hour before midnight
for working good.

663
00:51:00,733 --> 00:51:02,803
Half-hour after for evil.

664
00:51:03,053 --> 00:51:05,248
We'll need a little of both tonight.

665
00:51:05,533 --> 00:51:07,125
You got the bottle of water?

666
00:51:09,453 --> 00:51:11,171
Ain't been through no pipe?

667
00:51:12,453 --> 00:51:13,727
Give it to me.

668
00:51:18,493 --> 00:51:20,006
We got to make him...

669
00:51:20,253 --> 00:51:23,165
...Ioosen up on James.

670
00:51:26,893 --> 00:51:28,212
I need Shango...

671
00:51:28,893 --> 00:51:30,963
...and a little hungan.

672
00:51:43,853 --> 00:51:44,888
Come.

673
00:51:46,293 --> 00:51:47,408
Come!

674
00:51:52,373 --> 00:51:54,284
Tell me something about him.

675
00:51:55,093 --> 00:51:56,492
He tried to kill me?

676
00:51:56,733 --> 00:51:59,122
No, before then.
Something good.

677
00:52:00,933 --> 00:52:02,048
Your kind words...

678
00:52:02,293 --> 00:52:04,761
...take root, flower,
come back to bless you.

679
00:52:06,133 --> 00:52:07,964
Something that made him happy?

680
00:52:11,453 --> 00:52:12,568
His Camaro.

681
00:52:13,293 --> 00:52:15,932
He loved his Camaro.
He wouldn't let anyone near it.

682
00:52:16,173 --> 00:52:18,323
That car was his pride and joy.

683
00:52:18,973 --> 00:52:21,168
Keep talking. It's working.
It's working!

684
00:52:22,693 --> 00:52:25,651
He spray painted it flat black.

685
00:52:25,893 --> 00:52:29,169
You should've seen him.
He spent hours on that car, fixing it...

686
00:52:29,413 --> 00:52:30,368
...cleaning it.

687
00:52:30,613 --> 00:52:32,808
He painted racing stripes on it...

688
00:52:33,053 --> 00:52:34,771
...and all kinds of other things.

689
00:52:35,453 --> 00:52:36,886
He was very creative.

690
00:52:39,573 --> 00:52:41,723
That's something
most people didn't know.

691
00:52:41,973 --> 00:52:43,372
He was an artist.

692
00:52:44,133 --> 00:52:46,601
Just now,
when you were saying them things...

693
00:52:46,853 --> 00:52:48,844
...I felt him ease off.

694
00:52:49,653 --> 00:52:51,689
He heard you say you love him.

695
00:52:54,813 --> 00:52:57,327
That's preposterous.
He tried to kill me.

696
00:52:59,613 --> 00:53:02,002
He was working against you,
and now I know why.

697
00:53:02,413 --> 00:53:05,689
He wants you to tell the whole world
you hated him.

698
00:53:06,693 --> 00:53:09,002
Maybe they think you hated him
enough to kill him.

699
00:53:09,733 --> 00:53:11,689
If you do that, you go to jail...

700
00:53:11,933 --> 00:53:13,207
...and he know that.

701
00:53:14,813 --> 00:53:16,644
Most important thing:

702
00:53:17,733 --> 00:53:21,692
You got to beg that boy's forgiveness
each and every day.

703
00:53:27,453 --> 00:53:29,284
Time for evil.

704
00:53:34,013 --> 00:53:36,447
Quick, quick.
Tell me his name.

705
00:53:36,933 --> 00:53:38,332
Finley Largent.

706
00:53:38,973 --> 00:53:43,524
When you get home, write his name
7 times on a piece of paper.

707
00:53:43,773 --> 00:53:45,764
Connect all the names into one.

708
00:53:46,013 --> 00:53:48,049
Dot no I's, cross no T's.

709
00:53:48,333 --> 00:53:50,608
Fold it twice and put it in your pocket.

710
00:53:54,973 --> 00:53:56,088
Get a picture.

711
00:53:56,333 --> 00:53:59,052
Sew up the mouth with dove's blood.

712
00:53:59,293 --> 00:54:00,442
Blacken the eyes.

713
00:54:00,693 --> 00:54:02,729
Now go!
I got works to do.

714
00:54:06,693 --> 00:54:07,728
Boy!

715
00:54:08,613 --> 00:54:10,331
Take these words to heart.

716
00:54:12,333 --> 00:54:14,483
To understand the living...

717
00:54:14,813 --> 00:54:17,281
...you got to commune with the dead.

718
00:54:20,613 --> 00:54:21,523
Now go!

719
00:54:21,773 --> 00:54:23,570
And don't you dare look back!

720
00:54:53,613 --> 00:54:54,966
On the grave...

721
00:54:55,333 --> 00:54:56,971
Who is Dr. Buzzard?

722
00:54:57,253 --> 00:54:59,209
Minerva was married to Dr. Buzzard...

723
00:54:59,453 --> 00:55:02,843
...the foremost voodoo practitioner
in Beaufort County.

724
00:55:03,093 --> 00:55:05,891
You may not know it,
but you are deep in voodoo country.

725
00:55:06,653 --> 00:55:08,962
I don't believe
in the hocus-pocus of it...

726
00:55:09,213 --> 00:55:11,602
...but the spiritual force behind it.

727
00:55:12,213 --> 00:55:15,011
The shiny dimes were easy...

728
00:55:15,253 --> 00:55:17,926
...but the virgin water
was a trick or two.

729
00:55:18,573 --> 00:55:21,451
How do you know she wouldn't know
the difference if it was tap water?

730
00:55:22,573 --> 00:55:24,404
Not by looking or taste...

731
00:55:24,653 --> 00:55:27,451
...but she would've known
in an instant by looking at my face.

732
00:55:32,573 --> 00:55:33,767
I think...

733
00:55:34,013 --> 00:55:36,811
...the photo-doctoring
is going to be good therapy.

734
00:55:38,933 --> 00:55:41,401
What about the pleas
for daily forgiveness?

735
00:55:42,653 --> 00:55:46,532
No, I don't think that's
going to be happening. Definitely not.

736
00:55:54,333 --> 00:55:55,846
- Thank you.
- Have a good day.

737
00:55:57,173 --> 00:55:58,572
- Hey, you.
- How are you?

738
00:55:58,813 --> 00:55:59,962
- How you doing?
- Good.

739
00:56:00,213 --> 00:56:01,168
You work here?

740
00:56:01,653 --> 00:56:03,325
What you see is what you get.

741
00:56:03,573 --> 00:56:04,801
Nothing wrong with that.

742
00:56:05,053 --> 00:56:06,566
Gee, thanks.

743
00:56:25,333 --> 00:56:26,561
These are nice.

744
00:56:27,013 --> 00:56:29,004
You want to send some flowers?

745
00:56:30,133 --> 00:56:32,283
I think so.
I don't know, though.

746
00:56:32,533 --> 00:56:34,012
It's kind of complicated.

747
00:56:34,613 --> 00:56:35,887
For whom?

748
00:56:36,813 --> 00:56:38,007
What's she like?

749
00:56:38,253 --> 00:56:40,005
I don't know her that well.

750
00:56:40,253 --> 00:56:41,447
Roses are a favorite.

751
00:56:41,693 --> 00:56:43,604
A bit presumptuous.

752
00:56:43,853 --> 00:56:45,172
How about...

753
00:56:45,413 --> 00:56:46,289
...poinsettias?

754
00:56:46,533 --> 00:56:48,842
Perennials might
give the wrong impression.

755
00:56:49,453 --> 00:56:52,411
- Too long-term?
- Yeah, it's hard to say.

756
00:56:52,653 --> 00:56:54,564
This is complicated.

757
00:56:55,373 --> 00:56:56,806
How about petunias?

758
00:56:57,053 --> 00:57:00,841
They're pretty without
being presumptuous, smell nice...

759
00:57:01,093 --> 00:57:02,924
...and in 3 days you throw them out.

760
00:57:03,613 --> 00:57:05,365
Sound like what you're looking for?

761
00:57:09,533 --> 00:57:11,763
